extends ../layouts/modern-layout

block layout-content
  br
  //- Hero Section
  section.py-5
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-8.mx-auto
          h1.mb-3
            i.bi.bi-code-slash.me-2
            | Developing MarkHazleton.com
          p.lead.mb-4
            | A straightforward look at the tools and process behind building this site.
            | This documentation covers the technical stack, build process, and deployment pipeline.

          p.mb-4
            | Built on Node.js with Pug templates, hosted on Azure Static Web Apps, and deployed via GitHub Actions.
            | Based on the Start Bootstrap Resume template for rapid development.

  //- Main Article Content
  article#main-article
    .container
      .row
        .col-lg-8.mx-auto

          //- Table of Contents
          nav#table-of-contents.mb-5(aria-label='Table of Contents')
            .card
              .card-header
                h3.mb-0
                  i.bi.bi-list-ul.me-2
                  | Table of Contents
              .card-body
                ul.list-unstyled
                  li.mb-2: a.text-decoration-none(href='#foundation') Template Foundation
                  li.mb-2: a.text-decoration-none(href='#tech-stack') Technology Stack
                  li.mb-2: a.text-decoration-none(href='#build-process') Build Process
                  li.mb-2: a.text-decoration-none(href='#deployment') Deployment Pipeline
                  li.mb-2: a.text-decoration-none(href='#development') Development Workflow

          //- Template Foundation Section
          section#foundation.mb-5
            h2.h4.mb-3
              i.bi.bi-bootstrap.me-2
              | Template Foundation
            
            p.
              Started with the <a href="https://github.com/StartBootstrap/startbootstrap-resume" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Start Bootstrap Resume template</a> 
              for a solid foundation. This gave me a well-structured starting point and helped speed up initial development.

            p What made this template useful:
            ul
              li Clean, semantic HTML structure
              li Bootstrap-based responsive design
              li Good separation of concerns
              li Easy to customize and extend

          //- Technology Stack Section
          section#tech-stack.mb-5
            h2.h4.mb-3
              i.bi.bi-stack.me-2
              | Technology Stack

            h3.h5.mb-3 Core Technologies
            ul
              li <strong>Node.js 20</strong> - JavaScript runtime and build environment
              li <strong>Pug 3.0.3</strong> - Template engine for HTML generation
              li <strong>Sass 1.93.2</strong> - CSS preprocessing with Dart Sass
              li <strong>Bootstrap 5.3.8</strong> - CSS framework for styling
              li <strong>Bootstrap Icons 1.13.1</strong> - Icon library

            h3.h5.mb-3 Build Tools
            ul
              li <strong>PostCSS & Autoprefixer</strong> - CSS processing and vendor prefixes
              li <strong>Terser</strong> - JavaScript minification
              li <strong>Prism.js</strong> - Syntax highlighting for code blocks
              li <strong>Browser-sync</strong> - Live reloading during development

          //- Build Process Section
          section#build-process.mb-5
            h2.h4.mb-3
              i.bi.bi-gear.me-2
              | Build Process

            p.
              The site uses a unified build script that handles all compilation and optimization tasks.
              Everything runs through a single <code>build.js</code> script that coordinates different build steps.

            h3.h5.mb-3 Main Build Commands
            
            pre.bg-dark.text-light.p-3.rounded
              code.text-light.
                # Full build
                npm run build

                # Individual components
                npm run build:pug     # Compile Pug templates
                npm run build:scss    # Process SCSS files
                npm run build:scripts # Minify JavaScript
                npm run build:assets  # Copy and optimize assets

                # Development
                npm run start         # Build and serve locally
                npm run dev           # Watch mode with live reload

            h3.h5.mb-3 What the Build Does
            ul
              li Compiles Pug templates to HTML
              li Processes SCSS with Dart Sass and PostCSS
              li Minifies JavaScript with Terser
              li Generates RSS feeds and sitemap
              li Optimizes images and assets
              li Creates performance-optimized output in <code>/docs</code> folder

            p.
              The build system includes caching for faster rebuilds and parallel processing where possible.
              It automatically handles vendor prefixes, CSS minification, and asset optimization.

          //- Deployment Section
          section#deployment.mb-5
            h2.h4.mb-3
              i.bi.bi-cloud-upload.me-2
              | Deployment Pipeline

            p.
              The site deploys automatically to Azure Static Web Apps via GitHub Actions. 
              Changes pushed to the main branch trigger a build and deployment process.

            h3.h5.mb-3 How Deployment Works
            ol
              li Code changes are pushed to GitHub repository
              li GitHub Actions workflow triggers automatically
              li Node.js 20 environment is set up
              li Dependencies are installed with <code>npm ci</code>
              li Build runs with <code>npm run build</code>
              li Azure Static Web Apps deploys from <code>/docs</code> folder
              li IndexNow API is notified for search engine updates

            h3.h5.mb-3 Hosting Details
            ul
              li <strong>Platform:</strong> Azure Static Web Apps
              li <strong>Source:</strong> GitHub repository
              li <strong>Output Directory:</strong> <code>/docs</code>
              li <strong>Node Version:</strong> 20
              li <strong>Domain:</strong> markhazleton.com

            p.
              The deployment is fully automated - no manual steps required. 
              Azure handles SSL certificates, CDN distribution, and scaling automatically.

          //- Development Workflow Section
          section#development.mb-5
            h2.h4.mb-3
              i.bi.bi-laptop.me-2
              | Development Workflow

            p.
              Local development is straightforward with live reloading and automatic builds.
              The development server watches for changes and rebuilds as needed.

            h3.h5.mb-3 Local Development Setup
            ol
              li Clone the repository
              li Run <code>npm install</code>
              li Start development with <code>npm run dev</code>
              li Browser opens automatically with live reload

            h3.h5.mb-3 File Structure
            pre.bg-dark.text-light.p-3.rounded
              code.text-light.
                src/
                ├── pug/           # Pug templates
                ├── scss/          # SCSS stylesheets  
                ├── js/            # JavaScript files
                └── assets/        # Images and other assets
                
                docs/              # Built output (deployed)
                tools/             # Build scripts
                ├── build/         # Build tools
                └── audit/         # Performance auditing

            p.
              Browser-sync provides live reloading during development. 
              Changes to Pug, SCSS, or JavaScript files trigger automatic rebuilds and browser refresh.

            h3.h5.mb-3 Key Development Features
            ul
              li Build caching for faster rebuilds
              li Parallel processing where possible
              li Automatic sitemap and RSS generation
              li Built-in performance auditing tools
              li SEO validation and accessibility checks

          //- Summary Section
          section#summary.mb-5
            h2.h4.mb-3
              i.bi.bi-check-circle.me-2
              | Summary

            p.
              This setup provides a simple, effective workflow for building and maintaining a static site.
              The combination of Node.js build tools and Azure Static Web Apps makes deployment automatic and reliable.

            p Key benefits of this approach:
            ul
              li Fast local development with live reload
              li Automated deployment via GitHub Actions
              li Modern toolchain with good performance
              li Easy to maintain and extend
              li Built-in SEO and accessibility features

            p.
              The site uses standard web technologies with a focus on simplicity and maintainability.
              All the tools work together to create a smooth development experience.
